The epic document has been written to `/home/stephan/src/FairEmail/docs/epics/1.8-account-identity-folder-coloring-avatars.md`.

The document covers:
- **Entity coloring** — user-assigned colors on accounts, identities, and folders with a full-spectrum color picker
- **Color precedence** — identity → folder → account → default
- **Display modes** — stripe, dot, or none, with configurable stripe width
- **Color propagation** — message lists, navigation pane, conversation headers, action bars, context menus, widgets
- **Default folder colors** — Trash and Junk get automatic warning colors
- **Account avatars** — user-uploaded images per account
- **Sender avatar cascade** — contact photo → BIMI → Gravatar → Libravatar → favicon → third-party icon service → generated icon/identicon
- **Generated icon tuning** — saturation, brightness, and contrast threshold sliders
- **Favicon refinements** — partial scan, manifest scan, DMARC gating, custom URI templates
- **Privacy posture** — all network avatar sources off by default
- **7 open questions** covering ambiguities discovered during reverse-engineering
